Apple today provided developers and public beta testers with the release candidate versions of upcoming visionOS 2.5, tvOS 18.5, and watchOS 11.5 updates for testing purposes. The software is available a week after Apple <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/04/28/apple-seeds-watchos-11-5-beta-4/">seeded the fourth betas</a>.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2025/04/General-visionOS-watchOS-and-tvOS-Betas-Feature-Redux.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-999927" /><br/>
The betas are available to registered developers, and can be downloaded from the Settings app on each device. <br/>
<br/>
No notable new features have been found in any of the software updates so far, suggesting Apple is focusing on under-the-hood performance improvements and bug fixes. watchOS 11.5 will include a new Pride watch face option that goes along with <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/05/05/apple-watch-2025-pride-band/">this year's Pride band</a>. <br/>This article, &quot;<a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/05/06/apple-seeds-watchos-11-5-release-candidate/">Apple Seeds Release Candidate Versions of visionOS 2.5, tvOS 18.5, and watchOS 11.5</a>&quot; first appeared on <a href="https://www.macrumors.com">MacRumors.com</a><br/><br/><a href="https://forums.macrumors.com/threads/apple-seeds-release-candidate-versions-of-visionos-2-5-tvos-18-5-and-watchos-11-5.2456612/">Discuss this article</a> in our forums<br/><br/>